This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the language used in online forums and the challenge of detecting sarcasm in dialogue. It could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as online forums are a type of social network. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the societal implications of online communication. It may also be relevant to cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it discusses the development of automatic methods for detecting sarcasm. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it explores the use of statistical measures for achieving reliable sarcasm annotations.
